  <releases>
    <release version="2.beta.0" date="2022-10-26">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Added power settings</li>
          <li>Added options to import/export settings in the global menu</li>
          <li>Added an option to enlarge welcome message</li>
          <li>Added color to command-line output</li>
          <li>Turned main window adaptive</li>
          <li>Turned pop-up dialogs adaptive</li>
          <li>Updated "about" window to the new style</li>
          <li>Improved style of welcome message input field</li>
          <li>Renamed sidebar section "Miscellaneous" to "Login Screen"</li>
          <li>Renamed global menu option "Import user settings" to "Load session settings"</li>
          <li>The app, now, shows an error notification when trying to apply settings if logo
              is enabled and the chosen logo image does not exist on the system anymore</li>
          <li>Fixed "Apply Current Display Settings" feature not working on Ubuntu and Ubuntu-like systems</li>
          <li>Fixed some text showing up untranslated even if translation existed</li>
          <li>Fixed some typos</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>

